# Observability and debugging

## Correlation IDs (required)

Every log line in `server/` and `bridge/` must run inside a `tracing` span carrying:

- `trace_id` — UUID per inbound message or connection
- `session_id` — when known
- `player_id` / `client_id` — when known
- `seq` — when handling an event envelope

Propagate `trace_id` in the envelope optional field `payload._debug.trace_id` during dev (strip in release if needed).

## Debug bundle export

On `world.hash` mismatch, `event.rejected`, or session crash, server writes:

```
data/debug_bundle/<utc-timestamp>/
├── meta.json          # session, players, versions
├── last_events.jsonl  # last 200 events from log
├── acl_decisions.json # recent rejections with reason codes
└── hashes.json        # host vs reporter hash breakdown when applicable
```

Do not delete bundles without explicit user permission (`data-safety.mdc`).

## Session replay

`tools/replay` must be able to replay `event.log` from `--from-seq N` against a running server or mock consumer. Use for post-mortems without launching X4.

## In-game debug overlay

Extension Lua must expose a dev overlay (toggle via hotkey or menu) showing: connection state, RTT, last sent/applied `seq`, sim time, `world.hash`, last WS error code. Required before M1 is marked complete.

## Version handshake

First WS frame after connect must be `handshake` with `mod_version`, `proto_version`, `bridge_version`. Server responds with `handshake.ack` or `INCOMPATIBLE_VERSION` error — never proceed to game events on mismatch.
